Result: true  
Justification:  
The claim is "Gabriel improves the lives of his citizens." The P-type arguments collectively establish that Gabriel is ambitious, seeks power, and expands Roman territory. The rule for an ambitious Gabriel states he can either expand territory or improve lives, but not both. Since expansion is forced by his seeking power, improving lives is logically excluded. All P-type arguments are warranted and their justifications cover the necessary logical steps to conclude the claim is false. Moreover, each minimal semantic basis for the claim (e.g., Gabriel is ambitious, Gabriel does not expand territory) is addressed by at least one P-type argument's justification, satisfying C11.